00:27:15.580 --> 00:27:17.250
drop still more.

00:27:17.250 --> 00:27:23.990
For Al2O3, a trivalent cation
that goes down to 8.8, and

00:27:23.990 --> 00:27:25.840
that's really an average
because this

00:27:25.840 --> 00:27:27.720
is a hexagonal material.

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:33.670
And a second-rank property
tensor for a hexagonal crystal

00:27:33.670 --> 00:27:39.380
has to have two equal diagonal
elements and one independent

00:27:39.380 --> 00:27:41.695
diagonal element when you
